title: For Sale:  Type 41 Carcano & 91/59 Mosin
postcontent:
For Sale or Trade to Firearm Related

Top: Italian made WWII issued Type 41 Carcano in 6.5x52mm.  Rifle is 1944/45 manufacture at the Armaguerra Cremona factory.  The rifle is in overall very good shape and functional, some minor defects in the bluing and a few dings and minor scratches in the furniture.  The sporterization is typical of that performed by the importers in the 1960's. It comes with one en-bloc clip and ~10 rounds of surplus ammo.  Cash Value $140

Bottom: Russian made WWII issue Mosin Nagant model 91/59 carbine in 7.62x54r. Manufactured at Tula. If you are a Mosin Collector this is one of the harder ones to find.  The rifle is in great shape and functions and fires well.  A few very minor defects in finish and furniture. Comes with a little more than 100 rounds of surplus ammunition. Cash Value $250

Preferred trades are, Marlin/Glenfield lever actions, semi-auto rimfires in .22 short, shotguns in 12 gauge.  All trade offers and questions are welcome.  Located near Bowling Green, KY willing to travel a bit if necessary to complete a good trade.  Thanks for your time.

title: For Sale:  1958 Milled Chicom SKS With Ammo
postcontent:
For sale is a Chinese SKS in great condition. Serial # puts date of manufacture at 1958, possibly issued to VC soldiers during the Vietnam Conflict. Receivers at this time were milled instead of stamped, resulting in higher collectors value and probably lasting significantly longer with better build quality. It has a blade bayonet as opposed to the typical Norinco spike bayonet ("pig-sticker"), similar to the Russian SKS from which it was copied. All serial numbers are matching and bore is in fantastic condition. The gun is currently in a Romanian stock in fair condition, but I still have the (totally original) stock it came with when it was still packed in cosmoline, pictured below. Also included is a (non-original) sling, also pictured below. Finally, I'm adding 100 rounds of steel-cased 7.62x39mm Wolf Performance Ammo.

I'm sure you're aware that both the rifle and the ammo are very difficult to find right now with all the political turmoil. The SKS can be endlessly customized to suit any needs, with a wide array of aftermarket parts like synthetic adjustable and folding stocks, scope adapters, red-dot sights, etc etc. I've kept this one stock, meaning you can do with it what you wish while still being able to return it to its original state if you'd like. Goes from near-AK-clone to 1950s carbine in no time.

title: For Sale:  Kimmel AA Arms AP-9 AP9 Semi Auto 9mm pistol
postcontent:
"Here is a relic from the Ban- and Pre-Ban period of the 1990s. This is an AA Arms Pistol, model AP-9, manufactured from 1991 until 2001 in Indian Trail, North Carolina. It is a direct descendant and copy of the notorious Intratec KG-9 from the late 1970s. This was, to the best of our knowledge, the final clone of the KG-9. The KG-9 stirred up some action and warnings from the BATF, an agency that has always been more patient than many of us give them credit for, because that pistol fired from an open bolt. The KG-99 and this pistol, the AP-9, will release the sear from a bolt position that is only about halfway open. While the Intratecs had aluminum alloy lower frames, this one has a rough textured polymer lower frame. It is more ornage than its predecessor, with larger sights and a grooved muzzle barrel instead of a threaded barrel. Weight empty is about 3 1/2 pounds. Barrel length is 5 inches, and the included magazine holds 35 rounds". 
 !!!Ammo is not included!!!
Trade for assult style rifle or a few stock semi auto 22 rifles.
